text: Question: What to do if Cuts? Answer: Wash the cut properly to prevent infection and stop the bleeding by applying pressure for 1-2minutes until bleeding stops. Apply Petroleum Jelly to make sure that the wound is moist for quick healing. Finally cover the cut with a sterile bandage. Pain relievers such as acetaminophen can be applied.
